# Diff: ~/.codex/config.toml (DRAFT, do not auto-apply)

Source-of-truth read on 2026-04-24 from `C:/Users/mattm/.codex/config.toml`.

## Rationale

- **`sandbox_mode = "danger-full-access"` -> `"workspace-write"`.** Audit Week-1 #3 + Theme F. Today there is no boundary at all; combined with `bypassPermissions` on the Claude side, a poisoned skill can pivot to filesystem rewrite.
- **`[windows] sandbox = "elevated"` -> `"limited"` (or section removed).** "Elevated" is admin-equivalent on Windows. Nothing in the audited 30 days of Codex sessions actually required elevated rights for legitimate work. If something breaks, you'll see it in the first hour.
- **`approval_policy = "on-request"` -> kept.** This stays the right tradeoff with `workspace-write`; the model asks before crossing the boundary.
- **No changes to `[projects.*]` trust list.** Those are deliberate per-repo opt-ins and reflect the user's actual repo set.
- **No changes to `[mcp_servers.*]`.** EVOKORE-MCP, trigger, playwright stay wired as-is. The 3-of-5-children-erroring problem is in EVOKORE-MCP itself, not Codex config.

